sionID\":\"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6\",\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"toolu_b5d28c0c097b4ff2bed98892\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-012/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # Proposal: Session Storage Interface Implementation (AR-012)\\n2: \\n3: ## Summary\\n4: \\n5: Implement a session storage interface in `pkg/store` that provides Redis and Valkey backends for persisting sandbox metadata, with indexed queries for garbage collection based on expiry and last-activity timestamps.\\n6: \\n7: ---\\n8: \\n9: ## Purpose\\n10: \\n11: The session storage system provides persistent storage for sandbox session metadata in the agentcube project. It enables:\\n12: \\n13: 1. **Session persistence**: Store and retrieve sandbox information keyed by session ID\\n14: 2. **Garbage collection support**: Index sessions by expiry time and last activity for cleanup operations\\n15: 3. **Backend flexibility**: Support both Redis and Valkey storage providers via configuration-based selection\\n16: 4. **Singleton access**: Thread-safe initialization and global access pattern\\n17: \\n18: This implementation is required for AR-012 and supports the broader sandbox orchestration system documented in `sandbox-orchestration/design.md`.\\n19: \\n20: ---\\n21: \\n22: ## Scope\\n23: \\n24: ### In Scope\\n25: \\n26: - `pkg/store/store.go` - Core `Store` interface definition and `ErrNotFound` error\\n27: - `pkg/store/singleton.go` - Singleton pattern with `Storage()` and `initStore()` functions\\n28: - `pkg/store/store_redis.go` - Redis implementatio...\n  Line 32: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775852903941,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286ebe112ffeX3zH3bqYNGiKY6\",\"part\":