n-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md\"},\"output\":\"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-010/proposal.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: # AR-010 — Router 会话管理 Proposal\\n2: \\n3: ## Purpose\\n4: \\n5: Implement session management for the AgentCube Router component. This provides the core session resolution and sandbox creation logic that enables session-aware routing. The session management component:\\n6: \\n7: 1. **Session Resolution**: Reads `x-agentcube-session-id` header, looks up existing `SandboxInfo` from the Store when present\\n8: 2. **Sandbox Creation**: When session ID is empty, creates new sandboxes via Workload Manager HTTP API\\n9: 3. **Response Validation**: Parses `CreateSandboxResponse` from Workload Manager and builds in-memory `SandboxInfo` with session metadata\\n10: 4. **Store Integration**: Persists sandbox info to Store after successful creation for subsequent session lookups\\n11: 5. **Error Handling**: Maps Workload Manager errors to Router-specific error types (NotFound, Timeout, etc.)\\n12: 6. **Service Account Auth**: Attaches Kubernetes service account token for in-cluster Workload Manager authentication\\n13: \\n14: ## Scope\\n15: \\n16: ### In Scope\\n17: \\n18: | Deliverable | Description |\\n19: |-------------|-------------|\\n20: | `pkg/router/session_manager.go` | SessionManager interface implementation with GetSandboxBySession, createSandbox logic |\\n21: | `pkg/router/session_manager_test.go` | Unit tests for session resolution, sandbox ...\n\n/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z_logs/AR-013_ST-7.log:\n  Line 4: {\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1775851844356,\"sessionID\":\"ses_286fb62eeffeu87dFyPsA5cDKA\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_d7904b1ac0011VGFz7XtlztrF7\",\"messageID\":\"msg_d79049e07001mjNt4JdcnynuO5\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_286fb62eeffeu87dFyPsA5cDKA