{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853407761,"sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","part":{"id":"prt_d791c8b1c001IRmJFuLSA8zULk","messageID":"msg_d791c5b13001eEtqbflrwdHsZp","sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-812efb69d6cf4376a04ef92ef7460fbc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n8: \n9: ### Store interface (exact signatures)\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: package store\n13: \n14: import (\n15:     \"context\"\n16:     \"time\"\n17: \n18:     \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n19: )\n20: \n21: type Store interface {\n22:     Ping(ctx context.Context) error\n23:     GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n24:     StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n25:     UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error\n26:     DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n27:     ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n28:     ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n29:     UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error\n30:     Close() error\n31: }\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Errors\n35: \n36: ```go\n37: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Provider type constants (`singleton.go`)\n41: \n42: ```go\n43: const (\n44:     redisStoreType  string = \"redis\"\n45:     valkeyStoreType string = \"valkey\"\n46: )\n47: ```\n48: \n49: ### Singleton\n50: \n51: ```go\n52: var (\n53:     initStoreOnce = &sync.Once{}\n54:     provider      Store\n55: )\n56: \n57: func Storage() Store\n58: func initStore() error\n59: ```\n60: \n61: - `Storage()` calls `initStoreOnce.Do(initStore)`; on error `klog.Fatalf(\"init store failed: %v\", err)`.\n62: \n63: ### Sandbox document type\n64: \n65: Stored JSON unmarshals to `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo`:\n66: \n67: ```go\n68: type SandboxInfo struct {\n69:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n70:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n71:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n72:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n73:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n74:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n75:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n76:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n77:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n78: }\n79: \n80: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n81:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n82:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n83:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n84: }\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ## Redis implementation (`store_redis.go`)\n88: \n89: ### Struct\n90: \n91: ```go\n92: type redisStore struct {\n93:     cli                  *redisv9.Client  // github.com/redis/go-redis/v9\n94:     sessionPrefix        string\n95:     expiryIndexKey       string\n96:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Fixed key patterns\n101: \n102: | Field | Value |\n103: |-------|--------|\n104: | `sessionPrefix` | `\"session:\"` |\n105: | `expiryIndexKey` | `\"session:expiry\"` |\n106: | `lastActivityIndexKey` | `\"session:last_activity\"` |\n107: \n108: ### Connection options (`makeRedisOptions`)\n109: \n110: ```go\n111: return &redisv9.Options{\n112:     Addr:     redisAddr,     // REDIS_ADDR\n113:     Password: redisPassword, // REDIS_PASSWORD\n114: }, nil\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### Environment variables (Redis)\n118: \n119: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n120: |----------|----------|--------|\n121: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes | |\n122: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | Case-insensitive compare to `\"false\"` |\n123: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | Default `redis` |\n124: \n125: ### Operations summary\n126: \n127: | Method | Redis commands |\n128: |--------|----------------|\n129: | `Ping` | `PING` → expect `PONG` |\n130: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `GET session:{id}` |\n131: | `StoreSandbox` | Pipeline: `SETNX`, `ZADD session:expiry`, `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n132: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET key value XX` |\n133: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | Pipeline: `DEL`, `ZREM expiry`, `ZREM last_activity` |\n134: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:expiry -inf {before.Unix} LIMIT 0 limit` then pipeline GETs |\n135: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | `ZRANGEBYSCORE session:last_activity ...` then pipeline GETs |\n136: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `GET` (existence), then `ZADD session:last_activity` |\n137: | `Close` | `cli.Close()` |\n138: \n139: - `List*` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`.\n140: - `sessionKey(id)` → `sessionPrefix + sessionID`.\n141: \n142: ## Valkey implementation (`store_valkey.go`)\n143: \n144: ### Struct\n145: \n146: ```go\n147: type valkeyStore struct {\n148:     cli                  valkey.Client  // github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go\n149:     sessionPrefix        string\n150:     expiryIndexKey       string\n151:     lastActivityIndexKey string\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: Same string constants as Redis for prefix and ZSET keys.\n156: \n157: ### Connection options (`makeValkeyOptions`)\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: valkeyClientOptions := &valkey.ClientOption{\n161:     InitAddress: strings.Split(valkeyAddr, \",\"),\n162:     Password:    valkeyPassword,\n163: }\n164: ```\n165: \n166: Optional: `DisableCache` from `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, must be true); `ForceSingleClient` from `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, must be true).\n167: \n168: ### Environment variables (Valkey)\n169: \n170: | Variable | Required | Notes |\n171: |----------|----------|--------|\n172: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list → `InitAddress` |\n173: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n174: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `DisableCache` |\n175: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `\"true\"` enables `ForceSingleClient` |\n176: | `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n177: \n178: ### Operations summary\n179: \n180: | Method | Valkey API |\n181: |--------|------------|\n182: | `Ping` | `B().Ping()` → string `PONG` |\n183: | `GetSandboxBySessionID` | `B().Get().Key(key)` → bytes; `IsValkeyNil` → `ErrNotFound` |\n184: | `StoreSandbox` | `DoMulti`: `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity |\n185: | `UpdateSandbox` | `SET ... XX`; success requires `ToString() == \"OK\"` |\n186: | `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` | `DoMulti`: `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity |\n187: | `ListExpiredSandboxes` | `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(fmt.Sprintf(\"%d\", before.Unix()))`, `Limit(0, limit)` |\n188: | `ListInactiveSandboxes` | Same on `last_activity` key |\n189: | `UpdateSessionLastActivity` | `Exists` key → int64 must be 1; then `Zadd` |\n190: | `Close` | `vs.cli.Close()` then return nil |\n191: \n192: ### ZSET score semantics\n193: \n194: - **Expiry index:** score = `float64(sandboxRedis.ExpiresAt.Unix())` on store.\n195: - **Last activity:** score = `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`; `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`.\n196: \n197: ### MGET note (Valkey)\n198: \n199: - `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` builds all `session:{id}` keys and uses single `Mget`; comment states keys should be in same slot (deployment consideration).\n200: \n201: ## Dependencies (store package imports)\n202: \n203: - `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n204: - `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n205: - `k8s.io/klog/v2` (Valkey options logging)\n206: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types`\n\n(End of file - total 206 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` — versions in sandbox-orchestration `design.md`.\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/store`\n\n### Store interface (exact signatures)\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types\"\n)\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/design.md","time":{"start":1775853407735,"end":1775853407759}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853407764,"sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","part":{"id":"prt_d791c890b001fJFRomQN07YCRt","messageID":"msg_d791c5b13001eEtqbflrwdHsZp","sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f5c565150b8c4950b0ebef560321f0b7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Session Store Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n9: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n12: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n13: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n14: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n17: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n20: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n21: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n22: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n25: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Key construction\n28: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n29: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n30: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n33: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n36: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n37: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n38: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n41: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n42: \n43: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n44: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n45: - **WHEN** executed\n46: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n47: \n48: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n49: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n52: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n53: - **WHEN** called\n54: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n55: \n56: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n57: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n60: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n61: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n62: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n63: \n64: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n65: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n66: \n67: #### Scenario: Full removal\n68: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n69: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n70: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n71: \n72: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n73: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n76: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n77: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n78: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n81: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n82: \n83: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n84: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n85: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n86: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n87: \n88: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n89: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: Default redis\n92: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n93: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n94: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n95: \n96: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n97: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n100: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n101: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n102: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n103: \n104: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n105: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n108: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n109: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n110: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n111: \n112: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n113: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n116: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n117: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n118: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n\n(End of file - total 118 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Session Store Specification\n\n## Purpose\nPersist sandbox metadata keyed by session id, index sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection, and support Redis or Valkey backends selected by configuration.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n\n### Requirement: Not found semantics\nThe system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n\n#### Scenario: Get missing session\n- **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/session-store/spec.md","time":{"start":1775853407732,"end":1775853407762}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775853407767,"sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","part":{"id":"prt_d791c8ddb001TU4Suh4vh7q8az","messageID":"msg_d791c5b13001eEtqbflrwdHsZp","sessionID":"ses_286e3c540ffeVMlJLlenc31rWF","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-b1c4fbad01da4d1ebf6d103e25b7c99d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-012 Delta-Spec\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Define the session storage interface for the AgentCube project, providing a unified Store interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers for persisting sandbox metadata, indexing sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection.\n5: \n6: ## Base Specs\n7: - deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n8: - session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface, Redis/Valkey implementations, and key patterns\n9: - session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements and scenarios\n10: \n11: ## Requirements\n12: \n13: ### Requirement: Store interface contract\n14: The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n17: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n18: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n19: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID retrieves session data\n22: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists with sandbox JSON data\n23: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n24: - **THEN** it returns `*types.SandboxInfo` unmarshaled from the stored JSON\n25: \n26: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox persists new session\n27: - **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with non-zero `ExpiresAt`\n28: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n29: - **THEN** it executes SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: UpdateSandbox modifies existing session\n32: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n33: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n34: - **THEN** it updates only the session JSON value using SET with XX flag\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes session\n37: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n38: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` is called\n39: - **THEN** it deletes session key and removes session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: ListExpiredSandboxes returns expired sessions\n42: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n43: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n44: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from negative infinity through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: ListInactiveSandboxes returns inactive sessions\n47: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n48: - **WHEN** executed\n49: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n50: \n51: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity updates activity timestamp\n52: - **GIVEN** a session key `session:abc` exists\n53: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at)` is called\n54: - **THEN** it ZADDs the session id with score `at.Unix()` to the last_activity ZSET\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Close closes connection\n57: - **GIVEN** an open store connection\n58: - **WHEN** `Close()` is called\n59: - **THEN** the underlying client connection is closed\n60: \n61: ### Requirement: Not found semantics\n62: The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Get missing session\n65: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n66: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs\n67: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n70: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n71: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n72: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound`\n73: \n74: ### Requirement: Session key naming\n75: The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n76: \n77: #### Scenario: Key construction\n78: - **GIVEN** session id `abc`\n79: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n80: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc`\n81: \n82: ### Requirement: Expiry index\n83: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n86: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n87: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n88: - **THEN** ZADD adds session id with score `1234567890.0` to `session:expiry`\n89: \n90: #### Scenario: Delete removes from expiry index\n91: - **GIVEN** a session id in `session:expiry` ZSET\n92: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` succeeds\n93: - **THEN** ZREM removes the session id from `session:expiry`\n94: \n95: ### Requirement: Last-activity index\n96: The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp (or now if zero). `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to last-activity index\n99: - **GIVEN** a sandbox is being stored\n100: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n101: - **THEN** ZADD adds session id with score `time.Now().Unix()` to `session:last_activity`\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with explicit timestamp\n104: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Unix(1234567890, 0))` is called\n105: - **WHEN** the ZADD executes\n106: - **THEN** the score is set to `1234567890.0`\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity with zero time\n109: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called\n110: - **WHEN** the ZADD executes\n111: - **THEN** the score is set to `time.Now().Unix()`\n112: \n113: ### Requirement: StoreSandbox atomicity and validation\n114: The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n115: \n116: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n117: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n118: - **WHEN** called\n119: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n122: - **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}`\n123: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n124: - **THEN** error indicates expiry time is required\n125: \n126: #### Scenario: Atomic pipeline execution\n127: - **GIVEN** all parameters are valid\n128: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` executes\n129: - **THEN** SETNX, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity execute atomically; failure of any command fails the entire operation\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: UpdateSandbox semantics\n132: The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n133: \n134: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n135: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n136: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` runs\n137: - **THEN** Redis: SETXX returns false → error `key not exists`; Valkey: response not OK → same error class\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Update succeeds for existing key\n140: - **GIVEN** session key `session:abc` exists\n141: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` updates the sandbox\n142: - **THEN** the JSON value is updated and expiry/last-activity indices are unchanged\n143: \n144: ### Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID cleanup\n145: The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Full removal\n148: - **GIVEN** an existing session\n149: - **WHEN** delete succeeds\n150: - **THEN** GET session key returns not found and ZSETs no longer contain the member\n151: \n152: ### Requirement: List loaders tolerate missing keys\n153: When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing (Redis pipeline GET nil, Valkey MGET empty string) without failing the whole batch.\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member\n156: - **GIVEN** a session id in ZSET without a hash/string value\n157: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs\n158: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice\n159: \n160: #### Scenario: List with zero limit\n161: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0)`\n162: - **WHEN** called\n163: - **THEN** it returns `nil, nil`\n164: \n165: ### Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity preconditions\n166: The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n169: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", at)` is called\n170: - **WHEN** called\n171: - **THEN** error indicates session id cannot be empty\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Session existence verification\n174: - **GIVEN** session key does not exist\n175: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called\n176: - **THEN** it verifies existence via GET/Exists before ZADD and returns `ErrNotFound`\n177: \n178: ### Requirement: Provider selection via STORE_TYPE\n179: The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Default redis\n182: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n183: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n184: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Explicit redis provider\n187: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=redis`\n188: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n189: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n190: \n191: #### Scenario: Explicit valkey provider\n192: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n193: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n194: - **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed\n195: \n196: #### Scenario: Invalid provider type\n197: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=invalid`\n198: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n199: - **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating invalid store type\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive provider type\n202: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` or `STORE_TYPE=Valkey`\n203: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n204: - **THEN** provider is selected correctly (case-insensitive)\n205: \n206: ### Requirement: Redis environment and password policy\n207: The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n208: \n209: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n210: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set and `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n211: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n212: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n213: \n214: #### Scenario: Password optional when flag set\n215: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n216: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n217: - **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\n218: \n219: #### Scenario: Missing REDIS_ADDR fails\n220: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is not set\n221: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n222: - **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating REDIS_ADDR is required\n223: \n224: ### Requirement: Valkey environment and options\n225: The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n226: \n227: #### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses parsed\n228: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=host1:6379,host2:6379,host3:6379`\n229: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n230: - **THEN** `InitAddress` is `[]string{\"host1:6379\", \"host2:6379\", \"host3:6379\"}`\n231: \n232: #### Scenario: Optional client flags\n233: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true` and `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n234: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n235: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true and `ForceSingleClient` is true on `ClientOption`\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Password optional when flag set\n238: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` set, `VALKEY_PASSWORD` empty, `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n239: - **WHEN** Valkey store initializes\n240: - **THEN** initialization succeeds with empty password\n241: \n242: ### Requirement: Singleton access\n243: The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n246: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()`\n247: - **WHEN** they run concurrently\n248: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Fatal error on init failure\n251: - **GIVEN** initialization fails (e.g., connection refused)\n252: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n253: - **THEN** klog.Fatalf is called and the application exits\n254: \n255: ### Requirement: SandboxInfo type\n256: The system SHALL use `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types.SandboxInfo` as the document type for stored JSON.\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: SandboxInfo fields persisted\n259: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxInfo` with `SandboxID=\"sb123\"`, `SessionID=\"abc\"`, `ExpiresAt=time.Unix(1234567890, 0)`\n260: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called\n261: - **THEN** JSON is stored with fields `{\"sandboxId\":\"sb123\",\"sessionId\":\"abc\",\"expiresAt\":1234567890,...}`\n262: \n263: #### Scenario: SandboxInfo unmarshaled correctly\n264: - **GIVEN** stored JSON `{\"sandboxId\":\"sb123\",\"sessionId\":\"abc\",\"expiresAt\":1234567890,...}`\n265: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` is called\n266: - **THEN** returns `*SandboxInfo` with fields correctly unmarshaled\n267: \n268: ### Requirement: Store error definition\n269: The system SHALL define package-level error `ErrNotFound` with message `store: not found`.\n270: \n271: #### Scenario: ErrNotFound is exported\n272: - **GIVEN** the store package is imported\n273: - **WHEN** caller compares error\n274: - **THEN** they can use `errors.Is(err, store.ErrNotFound)` to check for not found errors\n275: \n276: ### Requirement: Provider type constants\n277: The system SHALL define constants `redisStoreType` and `valkeyStoreType` for provider type comparison.\n278: \n279: #### Scenario: Constants are defined\n280: - **GIVEN** the store package is imported\n281: - **WHEN** code checks provider type\n282: - **THEN** constants `redisStoreType = \"redis\"` and `valkeyStoreType = \"valkey\"` are available\n\n(End of file - total 282 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-012 Delta-Spec\n\n## Purpose\nDefine the session storage interface for the AgentCube project, providing a unified Store interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers for persisting sandbox metadata, indexing sessions by expiry and last activity for garbage collection.\n\n## Base Specs\n- deployment/client-go.md: Kubernetes client library for runtime API types (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n- session-store/design.md: Session store design including Store interface, Redis/Valkey implementations, and key patterns\n- session-store/spec.md: Session store specification with detailed requirements and scenarios\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Store interface contract\nThe system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n- **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775853407737,"end":1775853407765}}}}
